      "content": "but i dont see how you can separate them. if you start prioritizing \"shared cultural heritage\" or \"civic pride\" in a country, isn't it inevitable that people will eventually decide who belongs and who doesn't? it seems like you're saying we can have the benefits of a national identity without any of the actual nationalism, which sounds kind of impossible in the real world. isn't it more realistic to say that nationalism is just how humans naturally form cohesive groups?",
